				<h1 class="firstHeading">DoomEdit</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From modwiki</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/DoomEdit#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/DoomEdit#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div align="left" style="color: black; font-size: 18px; padding: 1px; border: 0px solid #000000;"><a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_bg.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_bg.png"><img src="/web/20090503012527im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/c/cb/D3square_bg.png" alt="Image:D3square_bg.png" width="50" height="50" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_bg.png" /></a> The information on this page is specific to <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Doom_3" title="Doom 3">Doom 3</a>.</div>
<hr />
<p>This page describes the Doom 3 specific functionality of the built-in map editor. For general information common to all <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Id_Tech_4" title="Id Tech 4">id Tech 4</a> games' editors please see the <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Map_editor" title="Map editor">map editor</a> page. DoomEdit can be started by typing "<a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Editor_%28console_command%29" title="Editor (console command)">editor</a>" in the <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Console" title="Console">console</a> or by starting Doom 3 with "+editor" in the shortcut's target command parameters. The best way to start DoomEdit is from its own shortcut:
</p>
<pre>d:\doom3\doom3.exe +set <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/R_fullscreen_%28cvar%29" title="R fullscreen (cvar)">r_fullscreen</a> 0 +set <a href="/web/20090503012527/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/R_multiSamples_%28cvar%29" title="R multiSamples (cvar)">r_multiSamples</a> 0 +editor
</pre>
